[Cassava brown streak virus disease (CBSD) is now the most economically
important biotic stress affecting cassava in the coastal lowlands of Eastern
and Southern Africa. Research efforts are being directed to increase the
availability and utilization of improved cassava varieties, and to strengthen
the national germplasm generation and deployment capacities in Kenya,
Tanzania, and Mozambique.
